<a href="javascript:card_browser(116)">The Pale Blade</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(981)">Helpless</a><br>
Gates of The Dead City<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(107)">Drawn to Its Power</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(982)">His Terrible Servants</a><br>
The Ring Draws Them<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(983)">It Wants to be Found</a> X4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(112)">Morgul Gates</a> X2<br>
In The Ringwraiths Wake X2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(106)">Dark Whispers</a> X2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(120)">Threshold of Shadow</a> <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(859)">All Veils Removed</a><br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont">    This is my first try at corruption, so throw me a frikkin bone here people, ok? <br>
<br>
   I like to bid at least 1, and go second.  Hopefully they will be playing with my sites, and will have to deal with a fierce TW witch king or other powerful  fierce nazgul at site 2 and a crapload of Nazgul at site 3.  The whole deck is designed to cycle, and out of the 5 or 6 games ive played with it so far, I have gone through the whole thing.  I like to keep one site behind my opponent, and late in the game, when my minions slow him down, race to victory! <br>
<br>
   The sites are kind of obvious, but I will explain them anyway... 1. pull aragorn, 2. kill frodo with fierce WK, or at least make him put on the ring and add some burdens, 3. give your opponent loads of black riders to play with, 4. add that one burden that may spark Toldea, Enquea or possibly a corruption. 5. i used eeny meeny miney mo to decide (Doh!) 6. Let your allies kick it to the minions with upped strength, 7. skip one of the most powerful phases in the game and let your minions live another day...8. use the high twilight to your own advantage, 9. draw the rest of your deck from all the burdens you added and kill him with your minions!<br>
<br>
   For the Free Peoples side, elven allies and their gear lead the way.  I tossed in some of the neato-burrito (a casey merry term) realms cards in there, like Lego&#39;s knives (awesome card!), The two new allies that let you remove twilight and kill minions in the regroup phase, Elrond and Galadriels rings (Elronds is a card drawing/opponent hand clogging tool) and Galadriel&#39;s, which is arguably the best deck cycling card out there (giving Gwemegil and They Are Coming a run for their money).  Gift of The Evenstar is another badass cycling method which gives Aragorn a boost in combat.  The fellowship is designed to be versatile depending on what kind of minions it is facing.  Uruks are just a pain, and everyone knows that.  This deck can soak a lot of wounds from Uruks, and heal lots, while your Nazgul kill their fellowship.  Not many people play Nazgul anymore, so they dont seem to be a really big problem fir my fellowship, but there is the essential Flaming Brands and Arwen to combat them.  Use The Last Alliance and weapons to boost your companions as always, and Play with the Realms Aragorn... he is just plain awesome!  You can effectively heal Borimir every turn for free, and Aragorn too if you didnt lose a skirmish with the citadel, giving you more exertions for his bow.  You will probably get Elrond out early with 3 of him in the deck, so you can draw lots of cards to set up your fellowship early.  The new Galadriel is cool as you can heal Legolas every turn for free, giving you a free aimed shot every turn.  Use Sam to remove burdens and get killed, and Secret Sentinels to get rid of Spies of Saruman or any other bad condtion under the sun...  <br>
<br>
   For the shadow side, I like to use the politician&#39;s method of world domination: corruption!  Use TW Wk, TW Enquea and Ostea to cause a burdened ring bearer and regular WK to cause massive damage.  Most of the minions in the deck rely on a large number of burdens, like Toldea, Enquea, and Nelya.  By the end of the game, with It wants to be found and all of the other burden adders in the deck, you should be able to kill their companions, if not burden frodo to death.  Many of the card choices are self-explanitory, like Morgul Gates, Helpless, Gates of the Dead city, Drawn to its power, and his terrible servants, and others rely on or aid in the practice of burden addding, such as: The ring draws them, In the ringwraiths wake, Dark Whispers, threshold of shadow, and all veils removed.  The pale blade is for O elbereth removement (is that a word?), and Mr. ferny for doing what he does best: nothing, and Cantea for those pesky flaming brands.  As far as strategy goes, try to play what you have, and for pete&#39;s sake, add burdens before you play toldea or enquea, they will be more effective that way.  Im assuming that since I posted this as advanced,  everyone reading knows how to play this type of deck, or at least has enough common sense to figure out how to do so.  Helpful comments are always welcome. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=24327"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24327" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
